cs.CV, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.HC 

The paper deals with the problem of layout parsing of historical Indic manuscripts using deep neural networks. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and deep learning (cs.DL). The paper also mentions downstream applications such as OCR and word-spotting, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper also introduces a custom web-based GUI annotation tool and a dashboard-style analytics portal, which are related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
